# Extension Analysis: Binary Stars and Galaxy Clusters

## Executive Summary

This document extends the previous α ∝ r^n scaling analysis to include binary star systems and galaxy clusters. The investigation tested whether these systems represent intermediate regimes between point-mass systems (planets) and extended mass systems (galaxies).

**Key findings:**
- Binary stars exhibit α ∝ r^+0.500, identical to planetary systems
- Galaxy clusters exhibit α ∝ r^+0.21, representing true intermediate scaling
- Complete hierarchy spans m = 0.00 to m = 1.88 across 10+ orders of magnitude in size
- Relationship n = (1-m)/2 connects α exponent to mass distribution universally

---

